The paper deals with the analysis of anonymous communication, which is a core topic in computer security (cs.CR). The analysis involves probabilistic modeling and information theory concepts (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the behavior of users in a network, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI). The analysis involves quantifying the worst-case anonymity of users, which can be seen as a problem in algorithmic analysis (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the Universally Composable framework, which is a theoretical framework for analyzing security protocols (cs.SI).
